Justice Anthony M. Kennedy is being thanked for his thirty years of service on the Supreme Court of the United States. He was nominated by President Reagan in 1987 and quickly confirmed without opposition. Justice Kennedy has been a significant figure in constitutional law, particularly in the areas of equal protection, separation of powers, and the First Amendment's guarantees of freedom of speech and religion. He has been a strong advocate for individual rights and limited government, leaving a lasting impact on American history.